><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39=
;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:1=
50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">Barring some unforeseen twist of fate, <strong>Shari Redston=
e</strong> will
likely soon announce that Paramount Global has agreed to settle a lawsuit b=
rought by President <strong>Trump</strong> against CBS News=E2=80=99s <em>6=
0 Minutes</em>=E2=80=94the latest in a string of settlements brokered by me=
dia organizations with the ostensible hope of avoiding protracted public le=
gal battles with the White House or unwanted federal intervention in their =
business dealings. As has been the case with Disney and Meta, Paramount wil=
l likely pay tens of millions of dollars to the Trump Presidential
Library. And while initial reports suggest the settlement talks may <em>not=
 </em>result in a deal, I am reliably told that Shari has already made up h=
er mind.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"=
margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Of all his recent lawsuits, Trump=E2=80=99s ca=
se against <em>60 Minutes</em> has the least merit, according to legal expe=
rts. In brief, CBS=E2=80=99s <em>Face the Nation</em> edited a clip of a <e=
m>60 Minutes</em> interview with <strong>Kamala Harris</strong> to
include one part of her answer to a question about the Middle East=E2=80=94=
a widespread and longstanding practice in television news=E2=80=94while the=
 actual <em>60 Minutes</em> broadcast included a different portion of her a=
nswer. Trump=E2=80=99s lawyers accused the network of =E2=80=9Cdeceptive do=
ctoring,=E2=80=9D a claim the network flatly denied. Meanwhile, legal exper=
ts called his lawsuit against the company =E2=80=9Cfrivolous=E2=80=9D and =
=E2=80=9Cridiculous,=E2=80=9D noting that CBS was well within its First Ame=
ndment protections.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;"><br/>From Shari=E2=80=99s vantage point, the practical =
concerns likely outweigh the ethical. She is on the cusp of closing a tortu=
red $8 billion deal to sell Paramount to Skydance=E2=80=94a deal that Trump=
=E2=80=99s Federal Communications Commission can block, or at least delay. =
Trump=E2=80=99s new F.C.C. chair, <strong>Brendan Carr</strong>, has said h=
e intends to investigate the <em>60 Minutes </em>matter as part of his revi=
ew of the merger, and has asked CBS News for unedited footage and a transcr=
ipt of
the Harris interview=E2=80=94which the company agreed to hand over on Frida=
y afternoon.=C2=A0<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Af=
ter presiding over the decline of her father <strong>Sumner</strong>=E2=80=
=99s media empire, holding on to it for far too long, and then <em>finally<=
/em> arriving at acceptable terms for a deal, Shari is understandably eager=
 to dispense with any eleventh-hour roadblocks. Meanwhile, the <strong>Elli=
sons</strong>, <strong>Gerry Cardinale</strong>, and
<strong>Jeff Shell </strong>are surely happy to have Shari do the dirty wor=
k <em>before</em> handing off the asset. <strong>Larry Ellison</strong>, af=
ter all, is a card-carrying member of Trump=E2=80=99s broligarchy, and Orac=
le is a participant in Stargate and an apparent contender for TikTok, if it=
 plays out that way. Shari=E2=80=99s making his life easier.</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">Presumably, a similar realpolitik logic persuaded
<strong>Bob Iger</strong> to greenlight Disney=E2=80=99s $16 million paymen=
t to the president-elect after he sued ABC News over <strong>George Stephan=
opoulos</strong>=E2=80=99s claim that Trump had been found civilly liable f=
or =E2=80=9Craping=E2=80=9D <strong>E. Jean Carroll</strong> when, in fact,=
 he had been found liable for =E2=80=9Csexual abuse.=E2=80=9D Sure, George =
was also likely within his First Amendment rights; even the judge in the ca=
se acknowledged that =E2=80=9Crape=E2=80=9D was the layman=E2=80=99s term, =
albeit not the legal one, for Trump=E2=80=99s actions.
But if you=E2=80=99re a $200 billion publicly traded company, and about to =
buy Fubo, why get involved in a costly and embarrassing legal battle=E2=80=
=94inevitably, George <em>and </em>Bob would have been forced to hand over =
their text messages and emails=E2=80=94when you can make the whole problem =
go away for a relative pittance? Ditto <strong>Mark Zuckerberg</strong>, wh=
o was well within his rights to terminate Trump=E2=80=99s social media acco=
unts for terms of service violation after January 6, but doesn=E2=80=99t wa=
nt to lose his
seat at Trump=E2=80=99s table, and thus yesterday agreed to hand over a $25=
 million settlement.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Alas, in business, realpolitik ver=
y often beats <em>idealpolitik</em>. Still, it=E2=80=99s possible to counte=
nance the corporate pragmatism while also acknowledging that this is all <e=
m>really bad</em> for the Fourth Estate. (For the good folks at CBS News, i=
t=E2=80=99s going to be hard to imagine that the Ellisons will
have their back more than Shari has, no matter how much Shell assures them.=
) On Friday, the Center for Journalism and Liberty characterized the expect=
ed Paramount settlement as =E2=80=9Ca payoff to the president whose F.C.C. =
has threatened to retaliate against coverage it doesn=E2=80=99t like by pul=
ling broadcast licenses and blocking mergers.=E2=80=9D Tough to argue with =
that.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;">And it=E2=80=99s already inspiring others to wield litigatio=
n against
media organizations. Trump=E2=80=99s former co-campaign manager <strong>Chr=
is LaCivita</strong> is preparing a defamation lawsuit against The Daily Be=
ast, demanding a full retraction and apology over an article that suggested=
 he was paid $22 million by the Trump campaign when, in fact, F.E.C. filing=
s show his advisory firm received $19.2 million from the Trump campaign, th=
e R.N.C., and related super PACs. Historically, such errors would have warr=
anted nothing more than a modest correction in italics.</p>
